New Records: Liam Walker now holds the all-time goal record for Gibraltar with six goals.
Key Match Events: Gibraltar scored an Olimpico from the corner flag to take an early lead.
James Scanlon scored Gibraltar's second goal in the 97th minute.
Nicolas Hasler scored a penalty for Liechtenstein in the 104th minute, resulting in a 2-2 draw.
Post-Match Reflections: Walker missed a penalty to retake the lead with only eight minutes to go.
The visitors found the back of the net in the 92nd minute, but the goal was wiped off due to offside.
Gibraltar's historic victory was not to be, however, as a Nicolas Hasler penalty in the 104th minute saw things end all square.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Gibraltar's first competitive goal in 713 days was scored against Georgia in September 2022.
The match ended in a chaotic and dramatic manner with multiple incidents and late goals.
